The paper deals with salient object detection in images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The images in question are 360$^\circ$ omnidirectional images, which are often used in virtual reality and immersive media, making the paper relevant to graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM). The proposed approach involves a distortion-adaptive module and a multi-scale contextual integration block, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
